The paper deals with information gathering in ad-hoc radio networks, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The focus on tree topology and the use of protocols suggests that the paper may also fall under distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of randomized algorithms and information theory concepts suggests that the paper may also belong to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
